    <item>
      <title>Math Acrobatics</title>
      <link>/post/links/hanoi/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 04 Jun 2018 09:33:04 +0200</pubDate>
      <guid>/post/links/hanoi/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;The youtuber 
&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCYO_jab_esuFRV4b17AJtAw&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;3blue1brown&lt;/a&gt; has a number of interesting posts.  however often he is a bit fast for me and it seems handwaving.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Recently he made a fantastic video about solving the 
&lt;a href=&#34;https://youtu.be/2SUvWfNJSsM&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;towers of hanoi&lt;/a&gt;.  I did already know it is easy to spell out the solution in terms of recursion.  However he showed some connection to binary and ternary numbers - which alone is funny.  And finally that the solution also traverses the Sierpinsky triangle in 
&lt;a href=&#34;https://youtu.be/bdMfjfT0lKk&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;part 2&lt;/a&gt; which is surprising.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I embeded the videos after the &amp;ldquo;post&amp;rdquo; fold for convenient watching.&lt;/p&gt;
